registration.description.text1: The Finnish National Certificates of Language Proficiency are language proficiency tests intended for adults. They assess language skills in practical situations where adults may generally need to speak, listen, write or read in a foreign language – at home or abroad.
registration.description.text2: The National Certificates of Language Proficiency assesses four skill components: speaking, listening comprehension, writing and reading comprehension.
registration.description.text3: Language proficiency assessments are made using a six-point proficiency level scale, which is commensurate with the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR).
registration.description.text4: Since June 2003, candidates have been able to demonstrate language skills required for acquiring Finnish citizenship by completing the National Certificate of Language Proficiency in Finnish or Swedish.
registration.description.title: National Certificates of Language Proficiency (YKI)
